http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Lawyer-demands-%E2%80%98suitable-legal-action%E2%80%99-against-CM/article14017558.ece

Accusing Chief Minister Siddaramaiah of assaulting the Commissioner of Ballari City Corporation, a city-based lawyer, Amrutesh, has lodged a complaint against him with the Vidhana Soudha police.In his complaint, the lawyer has demanded “suitable legal action” against the Chief Minister. The police said they had not registered an FIR and would consult legal experts.Incident deniedOn January 16, following a television clip, there were allegations that the Chief Minister had slapped the Commissioner, P.G. Ramesh. However both Mr. Siddaramaiah and Mr. Ramesh had denied the incident.